Text.SourceString: Is that… Is that you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=surprised>Wow! I almost didn’t recognize you in that getup.//<portrait=normal>Oh, so you’re the one moving into the lot, huh? That would explain the outfit.
Text.LocalizedString: Is that… Is that you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=surprised>Wow! I almost didn’t recognize you in that getup.//<portrait=normal>Oh, so you’re the one moving into the lot, huh? That would explain the outfit.

Text.SourceString: Right. It’s not just the town, you know. The inn isn’t as busy as it used to be.//Hopefully, with you moving in…it’s a sign of something good.
Text.LocalizedString: Right. It’s not just the town, you know. The inn isn’t as busy as it used to be.//Hopefully, with you moving in…it’s a sign of something good.

Text.SourceString: Oh, hey there! Nice to see a familiar face.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, hey there! Nice to see a familiar face.

Text.SourceString: Can I assist you with something?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I assist you with something?

Text.SourceString: People like to dismiss things they can't see.//What's the fun in that?
Text.LocalizedString: People like to dismiss things they can't see.//What's the fun in that?

Text.SourceString: Being alone isn't always bad.//Personal space is rarely a thing when you grow up with someone <Italic>sparkly</> like <NPCName>Suki</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Being alone isn't always bad.//Personal space is rarely a thing when you grow up with someone <Italic>sparkly</> like <NPCName>Suki</>.

Text.SourceString: Sure, energetic works too.//<NPCName>Suki</> is energetic.
Text.LocalizedString: Sure, energetic works too.//<NPCName>Suki</> is energetic.

Text.SourceString: I sometimes wonder if running this inn is the right move for me.//I don't know...
Text.LocalizedString: I sometimes wonder if running this inn is the right move for me.//I don't know...

Text.SourceString: Ah, here comes Monday…
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, here comes Monday…

Text.SourceString: *yawn*
Text.LocalizedString: *yawn*

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Suki</> and I split our responsibilities. I take the weekdays, and she takes the weekends.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Suki</> and I split our responsibilities. I take the weekdays, and she takes the weekends.

Text.SourceString: It’s pretty fair, I think… Right?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s pretty fair, I think… Right?

Text.SourceString: We monitor our guests daily and compile data for an end-of-season review.//That's the system our parents passed down to us.
Text.LocalizedString: We monitor our guests daily and compile data for an end-of-season review.//That's the system our parents passed down to us.

Text.SourceString: The mayor is always watching the economy.//He gets excited about the analysis when we go over what we learned in the past season and all that.
Text.LocalizedString: The mayor is always watching the economy.//He gets excited about the analysis when we go over what we learned in the past season and all that.

Text.SourceString: The inn usually gets more guests during festivals.
Text.LocalizedString: The inn usually gets more guests during festivals.

Text.SourceString: One of my hobbies is definitely reading!//What about you? What do you like to do in your spare time?
Text.LocalizedString: One of my hobbies is definitely reading!//What about you? What do you like to do in your spare time?

Text.SourceString: I also like to have meaningful discussions. Pick each other’s brains and share views…//You learn a lot of new things that way.
Text.LocalizedString: I also like to have meaningful discussions. Pick each other’s brains and share views…//You learn a lot of new things that way.

Text.SourceString: Here's a pro tip from a lifelong beach resident. Sometimes, you can stumble upon really rare seashells.//<portrait=happy>I’m talking rare as in expensive!
Text.LocalizedString: Here's a pro tip from a lifelong beach resident. Sometimes, you can stumble upon really rare seashells.//<portrait=happy>I’m talking rare as in expensive!

Text.SourceString: I’m pretty much free today. I usually pay the bills on Wednesdays…//That way, I can make sure that we don’t double pay.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m pretty much free today. I usually pay the bills on Wednesdays…//That way, I can make sure that we don’t double pay.

Text.SourceString: Think of it this way, the more people that are allowed access to paying the bills, the more chance that there’ll be mistakes – overpaying, missing invoices, all that.
Text.LocalizedString: Think of it this way, the more people that are allowed access to paying the bills, the more chance that there’ll be mistakes – overpaying, missing invoices, all that.

Text.SourceString: Our kitchen is free to use! It’s included in the room rate.//<portrait=normal>Guests can use our kitchen and anything we put out in the lobby.//But you knew that. You stayed in our inn that summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Our kitchen is free to use! It’s included in the room rate.//<portrait=normal>Guests can use our kitchen and anything we put out in the lobby.//But you knew that. You stayed in our inn that summer.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: When I first took over Coral Inn, I was pretty clueless. It definitely involves a lot.//But I imagine it's not quite as demanding as running a farm.
Text.LocalizedString: When I first took over Coral Inn, I was pretty clueless. It definitely involves a lot.//But I imagine it's not quite as demanding as running a farm.

Text.SourceString: How’s your week been so far?
Text.LocalizedString: How’s your week been so far?

Text.SourceString: Right! It's only Monday. Bit early for a week's progress report, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Right! It's only Monday. Bit early for a week's progress report, huh?

Text.SourceString: I took some questionable courses in university...classes on U.F.O, wine-making? It was a whole semester deal.//<portrait=normal>But actually, those classes were the most fun. Looking back, that should have been my major.
Text.LocalizedString: I took some questionable courses in university...classes on U.F.O, wine-making? It was a whole semester deal.//<portrait=normal>But actually, those classes were the most fun. Looking back, that should have been my major.

Text.SourceString: I didn't <Italic>like</> wine-making, but I did enjoy the class. Does that make sense?//Yeah, I'm confused too.
Text.LocalizedString: I didn't <Italic>like</> wine-making, but I did enjoy the class. Does that make sense?//Yeah, I'm confused too.

Text.SourceString: How are you doing today, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: How are you doing today, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Here's a thought for community improvement. Maybe the library could stock up on books about extraterrestrial life.
Text.LocalizedString: Here's a thought for community improvement. Maybe the library could stock up on books about extraterrestrial life.

Text.SourceString: Just putting it out there. There's definitely interest in that field.//<portrait=annoyed>Not only from me... let's see... Hmm… <NPCName>Noah</>.//And, Hmm…me?
Text.LocalizedString: Just putting it out there. There's definitely interest in that field.//<portrait=annoyed>Not only from me... let's see... Hmm… <NPCName>Noah</>.//And, Hmm…me?

Text.SourceString: I find it hard to believe we're the only life in the universe... There are some intriguing theories out there.
Text.LocalizedString: I find it hard to believe we're the only life in the universe... There are some intriguing theories out there.

Text.SourceString: Can you imagine what life is like on Mars? I would love to go there and see it for myself.//<portrait=concerned>It sounds a bit scary, though. Getting shot up to space.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you imagine what life is like on Mars? I would love to go there and see it for myself.//<portrait=concerned>It sounds a bit scary, though. Getting shot up to space.

Text.SourceString: If you’re not a caffeine person, a quick jog does the trick when you need to wake up.//<portrait=normal>It works on me.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re not a caffeine person, a quick jog does the trick when you need to wake up.//<portrait=normal>It works on me.

Text.SourceString: There is this magnificent rainbow seashell one time that <NPCName>Valentina</> brought home.//<portrait=surprised>Have you seen one of those?//<portrait=normal>Oh, it was so beautiful. I’m pretty sure it would sell for a lot too.
Text.LocalizedString: There is this magnificent rainbow seashell one time that <NPCName>Valentina</> brought home.//<portrait=surprised>Have you seen one of those?//<portrait=normal>Oh, it was so beautiful. I’m pretty sure it would sell for a lot too.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes we dye our sheets different colors to brighten things up…//That way they look new.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes we dye our sheets different colors to brighten things up…//That way they look new.

Text.SourceString: It’s all <NPCName>Suki</>’s idea, to tell you the truth.//<portrait=normal>If it were up to me, I’d just leave the sheets beige.//If it isn't broken, don't fix it.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s all <NPCName>Suki</>’s idea, to tell you the truth.//<portrait=normal>If it were up to me, I’d just leave the sheets beige.//If it isn't broken, don't fix it.

Text.SourceString: Hello, <PlayerName>$player</>! What brings you here?
Text.LocalizedString: Hello, <PlayerName>$player</>! What brings you here?

Text.SourceString: When we were kids, <NPCName>Suki</> and I used to dress the same to confuse our friends.//It didn’t always work, because we aren’t identical, but when it did, it was great!
Text.LocalizedString: When we were kids, <NPCName>Suki</> and I used to dress the same to confuse our friends.//It didn’t always work, because we aren’t identical, but when it did, it was great!

Text.SourceString: It was all <NPCName>Suki</>'s idea, naturally.//The 10-year-old me just went with the flow. She was much more adventurous than adult me.
Text.LocalizedString: It was all <NPCName>Suki</>'s idea, naturally.//The 10-year-old me just went with the flow. She was much more adventurous than adult me.

Text.SourceString: The universe is so big, don’t you think?//<portrait=happy>I mean, look at Earth. We haven’t even fully explored it yet.
Text.LocalizedString: The universe is so big, don’t you think?//<portrait=happy>I mean, look at Earth. We haven’t even fully explored it yet.

Text.SourceString: We seem to keep finding new species of animals… On land, in the ocean! Ancient fish. Gosh.//<portrait=surprised>What else is out there?!//<portrait=happy>Could there be life on other planets? I think so.
Text.LocalizedString: We seem to keep finding new species of animals… On land, in the ocean! Ancient fish. Gosh.//<portrait=surprised>What else is out there?!//<portrait=happy>Could there be life on other planets? I think so.

Text.SourceString: I could be wrong… But I’m keeping my mind open.//<portrait=happy>Let’s see where it gets me.
Text.LocalizedString: I could be wrong… But I’m keeping my mind open.//<portrait=happy>Let’s see where it gets me.

Text.SourceString: I don’t see why I should buy my own camera.//<portrait=normal>I don't want to spend money on a camera when I can just borrow <NPCName>Macy</>’s.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t see why I should buy my own camera.//<portrait=normal>I don't want to spend money on a camera when I can just borrow <NPCName>Macy</>’s.

Text.SourceString: Ah, she doesn’t mind anyway. Besides, it’s not like I use it every day…//<portrait=surprised>Maybe three times a year, tops!
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, she doesn’t mind anyway. Besides, it’s not like I use it every day…//<portrait=surprised>Maybe three times a year, tops!

Text.SourceString: Morning jogs can be fun, especially with a partner.
Text.LocalizedString: Morning jogs can be fun, especially with a partner.

Text.SourceString: As soon as <NPCName>Suki</> was back in town, our parents decided to retire early.//They didn’t think the inn had enough work for four people.
Text.LocalizedString: As soon as <NPCName>Suki</> was back in town, our parents decided to retire early.//They didn’t think the inn had enough work for four people.

Text.SourceString: You see, my sis used to live in Labuan Bajo, the little town on the other side of Coral Island, with her ex-husband.//<portrait=sad>But since the, errr, separation, she moved back here.
Text.LocalizedString: You see, my sis used to live in Labuan Bajo, the little town on the other side of Coral Island, with her ex-husband.//<portrait=sad>But since the, errr, separation, she moved back here.

Text.SourceString: The internet has way too many poorly sourced articles about flying saucers… Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: The internet has way too many poorly sourced articles about flying saucers… Hmm…

Text.SourceString: It’s a bit hard to sort through them all.//If only there were a filter that showed just certain publications…
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a bit hard to sort through them all.//If only there were a filter that showed just certain publications…

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Rafael</>? Yeah, he might be at the inn today.//He does visit us on Sunday when he can.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Rafael</>? Yeah, he might be at the inn today.//He does visit us on Sunday when he can.

Text.SourceString: He sure is dedicated. <NPCName>Rafael</> visits <NPCName>Valentina</> on weekends and makes sure she’s all right.
Text.LocalizedString: He sure is dedicated. <NPCName>Rafael</> visits <NPCName>Valentina</> on weekends and makes sure she’s all right.

Text.SourceString: The whole Sanchez family is very caring and tight-knit. <NPCName>Rafael</>, <NPCName>Antonio</>, <NPCName>Pablo</>...all of them.
Text.LocalizedString: The whole Sanchez family is very caring and tight-knit. <NPCName>Rafael</>, <NPCName>Antonio</>, <NPCName>Pablo</>...all of them.

Text.SourceString: I still think of them as my cousins.//Because in my heart, we are.
Text.LocalizedString: I still think of them as my cousins.//Because in my heart, we are.

Text.SourceString: The cherry blossoms look beautiful this time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: The cherry blossoms look beautiful this time of year.

Text.SourceString: This time of year, you can find fresh wasabi by the river…
Text.LocalizedString: This time of year, you can find fresh wasabi by the river…

Text.SourceString: Oh, you didn’t find any, you said?//<portrait=normal>Animals might have eaten them already. But have you tried by the river in the forest?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you didn’t find any, you said?//<portrait=normal>Animals might have eaten them already. But have you tried by the river in the forest?

Text.SourceString: Ah… I kinda miss the snow already.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah… I kinda miss the snow already.

Text.SourceString: On my morning walk the other day, I saw people gathering bamboo shoots near the lake.//You should check it out.
Text.LocalizedString: On my morning walk the other day, I saw people gathering bamboo shoots near the lake.//You should check it out.

Text.SourceString: Are you planning on planting pineapples this Summer?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you planning on planting pineapples this Summer?

Text.SourceString: They’re all right. I was just curious…//But I heard that <NPCName>Joko</> loves pineapples. One time he gave us some as a souvenir from his trip.
Text.LocalizedString: They’re all right. I was just curious…//But I heard that <NPCName>Joko</> loves pineapples. One time he gave us some as a souvenir from his trip.

Text.SourceString: I’m so happy Spring is almost over, because it means Summer is right around the corner. I love the longer days!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so happy Spring is almost over, because it means Summer is right around the corner. I love the longer days!

Text.SourceString: There’s something cheerful about the flowers in Spring. I know <NPCName>Suki</> can’t get enough of them.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s something cheerful about the flowers in Spring. I know <NPCName>Suki</> can’t get enough of them.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I made it through another Winter.//<portrait=happy>Now I can look forward to Summer!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I made it through another Winter.//<portrait=happy>Now I can look forward to Summer!

Text.SourceString: I’m just counting the days until Summer is here, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m just counting the days until Summer is here, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I don’t usually love the color pink, but I make an exception for cherry blossoms.//<portrait=happy>They’re just so beautiful.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t usually love the color pink, but I make an exception for cherry blossoms.//<portrait=happy>They’re just so beautiful.

Text.SourceString: Living with <NPCName>Suki</> in Spring has pros and cons.//<portrait=happy>Pro: I barely have to clean anything, because she goes on a cleaning spree.//<portrait=annoyed>Con: She’s even more overbearing and annoying than usual.
Text.LocalizedString: Living with <NPCName>Suki</> in Spring has pros and cons.//<portrait=happy>Pro: I barely have to clean anything, because she goes on a cleaning spree.//<portrait=annoyed>Con: She’s even more overbearing and annoying than usual.

Text.SourceString: Summer, finally! Now I can read outside as much as I want.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer, finally! Now I can read outside as much as I want.

Text.SourceString: Do you know what Summer is good for? Spending time outside, eating tons of minced jackfruit pies, going to the beach – all that good stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know what Summer is good for? Spending time outside, eating tons of minced jackfruit pies, going to the beach – all that good stuff.

Text.SourceString: I’ll read anywhere, but there’s something about reading outside in the Summer sun that’s more relaxing.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll read anywhere, but there’s something about reading outside in the Summer sun that’s more relaxing.

Text.SourceString: Easily the best thing about Summer is the abundance of jackfruit. I can make as many minced jackfruit pies as I want!
Text.LocalizedString: Easily the best thing about Summer is the abundance of jackfruit. I can make as many minced jackfruit pies as I want!

Text.SourceString: I’m excited about the Beach Cleanup Festival later this season. Are you?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m excited about the Beach Cleanup Festival later this season. Are you?

Text.SourceString: It’s easier to do my…research in Summer.//I can stay out longer to see if there’s anything strange on the island.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s easier to do my…research in Summer.//I can stay out longer to see if there’s anything strange on the island.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to see the community come together. It’s one of the reasons I love the Beach Cleanup Festival.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to see the community come together. It’s one of the reasons I love the Beach Cleanup Festival.

Text.SourceString: I wish <NPCName>Noah</> would come to the forest with me to help with my research, but he just wants to stay at the beach all day.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish <NPCName>Noah</> would come to the forest with me to help with my research, but he just wants to stay at the beach all day.

Text.SourceString: I love seeing the daisies popping up everywhere. It practically screams Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: I love seeing the daisies popping up everywhere. It practically screams Summer.

Text.SourceString: Why can’t Summer be longer? I haven’t finished my reading yet!
Text.LocalizedString: Why can’t Summer be longer? I haven’t finished my reading yet!

Text.SourceString: It’s the last week of Fall, and do you know what that means?//<portrait=annoyed>We have to prepare the inn for Winter. Ugh.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s the last week of Fall, and do you know what that means?//<portrait=annoyed>We have to prepare the inn for Winter. Ugh.

Text.SourceString: Fall is so pretty, isn’t it? Now, if only it were a bit warmer…
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is so pretty, isn’t it? Now, if only it were a bit warmer…

Text.SourceString: Brrrr. It’s starting to get cold. I’ll have to do my reading inside soon.
Text.LocalizedString: Brrrr. It’s starting to get cold. I’ll have to do my reading inside soon.

Text.SourceString: I miss Summer already…
Text.LocalizedString: I miss Summer already…

Text.SourceString: It’s so chilly…
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so chilly…

Text.SourceString: When will this Winter be over?
Text.LocalizedString: When will this Winter be over?

Text.SourceString: The only good thing about Winter is it’s when our birthday is.//<portrait=annoyed>Everything else I can do without.
Text.LocalizedString: The only good thing about Winter is it’s when our birthday is.//<portrait=annoyed>Everything else I can do without.

Text.SourceString: I asked my parents <Italic>and</> <NPCName>Suki</> if we could just close the inn for Winter, but they shot me down. Many times.//<portrait=annoyed>You think a broken air conditioner is a problem, wait until you deal with a guest complaining about the heater.
Text.LocalizedString: I asked my parents <Italic>and</> <NPCName>Suki</> if we could just close the inn for Winter, but they shot me down. Many times.//<portrait=annoyed>You think a broken air conditioner is a problem, wait until you deal with a guest complaining about the heater.

Text.SourceString: I’d close the inn all Winter if it were up to me. But we can’t.//Something about being the only inn in town. Ugh.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d close the inn all Winter if it were up to me. But we can’t.//Something about being the only inn in town. Ugh.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to the New Year’s Eve Festival.//It’s so fun and festive, but it also means Winter is officially over.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to the New Year’s Eve Festival.//It’s so fun and festive, but it also means Winter is officially over.

Text.SourceString: It can be a bit of a bummer to have a birthday so close to a festival, but our parents made sure we didn’t feel left out when we were younger.
Text.LocalizedString: It can be a bit of a bummer to have a birthday so close to a festival, but our parents made sure we didn’t feel left out when we were younger.

Text.SourceString: The snow is pretty, I’ll admit. But does it have to be so cold?
Text.LocalizedString: The snow is pretty, I’ll admit. But does it have to be so cold?

Text.SourceString: If I ever leave this town, the festival would be one thing that I’d miss.
Text.LocalizedString: If I ever leave this town, the festival would be one thing that I’d miss.

Text.SourceString: I love seeing all these pretty Summer flowers around the island.//Diversity is beautiful, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: I love seeing all these pretty Summer flowers around the island.//Diversity is beautiful, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: Make sure to use enough sunscreen for the beach cleanup tomorrow, <PlayerName>$player</>. We’ll be in the sun the whole day.
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure to use enough sunscreen for the beach cleanup tomorrow, <PlayerName>$player</>. We’ll be in the sun the whole day.

Text.SourceString: There’s a swimming contest too.//<NPCName>Sunny’s</> going to be the winner again, I bet. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a swimming contest too.//<NPCName>Sunny’s</> going to be the winner again, I bet. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: Ah, the beach looks so clean. But I hope we don’t forget there’s still so much trash in the sea and the river.//We still need to change our lifestyle to stop this from happening.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, the beach looks so clean. But I hope we don’t forget there’s still so much trash in the sea and the river.//We still need to change our lifestyle to stop this from happening.

Text.SourceString: Everyone did such a great job yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: Everyone did such a great job yesterday.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if <NPCName>Ben</> has left on his trip yet…
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if <NPCName>Ben</> has left on his trip yet…

Text.SourceString: I should head to <NPCName>Ben’s</> next week. I need to catch him before he leaves for his trip.
Text.LocalizedString: I should head to <NPCName>Ben’s</> next week. I need to catch him before he leaves for his trip.

Text.SourceString: The leaves were crunchy on my walk this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: The leaves were crunchy on my walk this morning.

Text.SourceString: I love walking through the leaves. Do you ever do that?
Text.LocalizedString: I love walking through the leaves. Do you ever do that?

Text.SourceString: I have to start working on a new marketing plan for Winter…
Text.LocalizedString: I have to start working on a new marketing plan for Winter…

Text.SourceString: They give out free mooncakes at the Harvest Festival.//They’re <NPCName>Betty’s</>, so they’re good, for sure!
Text.LocalizedString: They give out free mooncakes at the Harvest Festival.//They’re <NPCName>Betty’s</>, so they’re good, for sure!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Dinda</> and <NPCName>Joko</> are very talented. They made some of our cabinets.//I wonder how long it took them to get so good at carpentry.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Dinda</> and <NPCName>Joko</> are very talented. They made some of our cabinets.//I wonder how long it took them to get so good at carpentry.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Noah</> wanted to open a booth at the Harvest Festival with the information we gathered on flying saucers.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Noah</> wanted to open a booth at the Harvest Festival with the information we gathered on flying saucers.

Text.SourceString: Nope! I’m not doing that. Thankfully, he changed his mind.
Text.LocalizedString: Nope! I’m not doing that. Thankfully, he changed his mind.

Text.SourceString: The inn got a bad review last year. A couple complained about the broken heater in their room. So we have to make sure it’s working this year.//<portrait=sad>It could be bad for business otherwise.
Text.LocalizedString: The inn got a bad review last year. A couple complained about the broken heater in their room. So we have to make sure it’s working this year.//<portrait=sad>It could be bad for business otherwise.

Text.SourceString: I had my green tea too late today.//<portrait=sad>I don’t think I’ll be able to sleep tonight…
Text.LocalizedString: I had my green tea too late today.//<portrait=sad>I don’t think I’ll be able to sleep tonight…

Text.SourceString: I couldn’t get to sleep until 1 am. I might have had too much caffeine yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: I couldn’t get to sleep until 1 am. I might have had too much caffeine yesterday.

Text.SourceString: I like dinner parties, but sometimes people can wear you out…
Text.LocalizedString: I like dinner parties, but sometimes people can wear you out…

Text.SourceString: Is it too early to say Happy New Year?
Text.LocalizedString: Is it too early to say Happy New Year?

Text.SourceString: This weather makes me sleepy…
Text.LocalizedString: This weather makes me sleepy…

Text.SourceString: This weather makes me sleepy…
Text.LocalizedString: This weather makes me sleepy…

Text.SourceString: Meh… A little rain is fine with me…
Text.LocalizedString: Meh… A little rain is fine with me…

Text.SourceString: I see you don’t mind it either…
Text.LocalizedString: I see you don’t mind it either…

Text.SourceString: *<NPCName>Alice</> is ignoring you*
Text.LocalizedString: *<NPCName>Alice</> is ignoring you*

Text.SourceString: Quite a storm, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: Quite a storm, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: I hope it doesn’t turn into a storm like last time! We can’t afford to install a new heating system every Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it doesn’t turn into a storm like last time! We can’t afford to install a new heating system every Winter.

Text.SourceString: If this Winter gets any colder, I’m afraid we’ll start losing business.
Text.LocalizedString: If this Winter gets any colder, I’m afraid we’ll start losing business.

Text.SourceString: …I hope it doesn’t get to that point.
Text.LocalizedString: …I hope it doesn’t get to that point.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to put all the extra blankets up front. In case any of our guests need one.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to put all the extra blankets up front. In case any of our guests need one.

Text.SourceString: Do you need a room?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you need a room?

Text.SourceString: *<NPCName>Alice</> seems to be working*
Text.LocalizedString: *<NPCName>Alice</> seems to be working*

Text.SourceString: I just updated our point-of-sale system. Let’s see how it works!
Text.LocalizedString: I just updated our point-of-sale system. Let’s see how it works!

Text.SourceString: I’m a little busy right now…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a little busy right now…

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna get ready for bed, then read for a bit…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna get ready for bed, then read for a bit…

Text.SourceString: We offer wine in the evening and a fresh fruit bar in the morning…//<portrait=happy>I think that should be enough, don’t you?
Text.LocalizedString: We offer wine in the evening and a fresh fruit bar in the morning…//<portrait=happy>I think that should be enough, don’t you?

Text.SourceString: Someone on the internet named Sarahhh with three H’s said that she loved the inn!//And couldn’t wait to come back.
Text.LocalizedString: Someone on the internet named Sarahhh with three H’s said that she loved the inn!//And couldn’t wait to come back.

Text.SourceString: Just trying to respond to online reviewers. Then I’m going to manage our social media marketing.
Text.LocalizedString: Just trying to respond to online reviewers. Then I’m going to manage our social media marketing.

Text.SourceString: Don’t even try to tell <NPCName>Suki</> to sit still and work the desk for too long.//She won’t be able to do it.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t even try to tell <NPCName>Suki</> to sit still and work the desk for too long.//She won’t be able to do it.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Suki</>’s too active for a desk job.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Suki</>’s too active for a desk job.

Text.SourceString: I think it may be a good idea to rent out sales space in the lobby.
Text.LocalizedString: I think it may be a good idea to rent out sales space in the lobby.

Text.SourceString: I meant, like, <NPCName>Luke</>  for instance. He could rent some space over there, by the door, and sell electronics.
Text.LocalizedString: I meant, like, <NPCName>Luke</>  for instance. He could rent some space over there, by the door, and sell electronics.

Text.SourceString: Or – oh! The vineyard! They could sell wine here.
Text.LocalizedString: Or – oh! The vineyard! They could sell wine here.

Text.SourceString: Looking for one of our guests, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>You don’t need my permission. Go ahead and find them.
Text.LocalizedString: Looking for one of our guests, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>You don’t need my permission. Go ahead and find them.

Text.SourceString: Thanks for asking, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Thanks for asking, though.

Text.SourceString: Sorry, I can’t open any locked doors for you. If it’s closed, there’s nothing I can help you with.//I guess my best advice is just to talk to the guest.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry, I can’t open any locked doors for you. If it’s closed, there’s nothing I can help you with.//I guess my best advice is just to talk to the guest.

Text.SourceString: Once you get to know them better, maybe they’ll let you in their room.
Text.LocalizedString: Once you get to know them better, maybe they’ll let you in their room.

Text.SourceString: Yes? I don’t want to be rude, but I’m a little too tired to chat…
Text.LocalizedString: Yes? I don’t want to be rude, but I’m a little too tired to chat…

Text.SourceString: Did you just have your morning walk too? I like how quiet it is in the morning.//Right before everyone wakes up. It’s just you and the birds.
Text.LocalizedString: Did you just have your morning walk too? I like how quiet it is in the morning.//Right before everyone wakes up. It’s just you and the birds.

Text.SourceString: I have to work today. I’m going straight to the inn after this.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to work today. I’m going straight to the inn after this.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Karen</> used to have a room at the inn before she rented that space over there.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Karen</> used to have a room at the inn before she rented that space over there.

Text.SourceString: I didn’t know then that she was going to install drills around the island…//She was always very secretive. Never really looked like a tourist, either.
Text.LocalizedString: I didn’t know then that she was going to install drills around the island…//She was always very secretive. Never really looked like a tourist, either.

Text.SourceString: Did you hear about the light phenomenon over on Turtle Island?
Text.LocalizedString: Did you hear about the light phenomenon over on Turtle Island?

Text.SourceString: I do like to read about odd phenomena all over the world.//<portrait=surprised>It fascinates me.
Text.LocalizedString: I do like to read about odd phenomena all over the world.//<portrait=surprised>It fascinates me.

Text.SourceString: Fancy meeting you here!//<portrait=happy>I only ever see <NPCName>Ben</> and sometimes a monkey or two.
Text.LocalizedString: Fancy meeting you here!//<portrait=happy>I only ever see <NPCName>Ben</> and sometimes a monkey or two.

Text.SourceString: Are you heading to the cavern?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you heading to the cavern?

Text.SourceString: Hmm… I think I’ll walk through town on my way home.//<portrait=normal>I have to make a quick stop at the library.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… I think I’ll walk through town on my way home.//<portrait=normal>I have to make a quick stop at the library.

Text.SourceString: My granddad told me that his friend saw a bright green light deep in the forest. He was pretty sure it was an alien spaceship.
Text.LocalizedString: My granddad told me that his friend saw a bright green light deep in the forest. He was pretty sure it was an alien spaceship.

Text.SourceString: Could be nothing, but who knows…//<portrait=normal>I might see something one of these days and decide for myself.
Text.LocalizedString: Could be nothing, but who knows…//<portrait=normal>I might see something one of these days and decide for myself.

Text.SourceString: It’s such a different vibe in here compared to the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s such a different vibe in here compared to the inn.

Text.SourceString: Some people have claimed to see a figure over the lake…//<portrait=happy>The elders call it the Goddess…
Text.LocalizedString: Some people have claimed to see a figure over the lake…//<portrait=happy>The elders call it the Goddess…

Text.SourceString: What if…//<portrait=annoyed>What if she’s not a spiritual figure like the locals believe, but actually from another planet?!
Text.LocalizedString: What if…//<portrait=annoyed>What if she’s not a spiritual figure like the locals believe, but actually from another planet?!

Text.SourceString: If you're interested in aliens, you should read this book by Professor Kiep.//He has interesting theories about ET intelligence. I read it back in university...
Text.LocalizedString: If you're interested in aliens, you should read this book by Professor Kiep.//He has interesting theories about ET intelligence. I read it back in university...

Text.SourceString: Who orders the books inside the library, I wonder?//There are way too many cookbooks.
Text.LocalizedString: Who orders the books inside the library, I wonder?//There are way too many cookbooks.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if the library has any new books. I’ve been reading the same old books.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if the library has any new books. I’ve been reading the same old books.

Text.SourceString: I’m not being fair. It’s my own fault because I like to reread the same old books.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not being fair. It’s my own fault because I like to reread the same old books.

Text.SourceString: Can you smell the salt? Hmmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Can you smell the salt? Hmmm…

Text.SourceString: I’ll head back to the inn soon. I just wanna get some new books first at the library.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll head back to the inn soon. I just wanna get some new books first at the library.

Text.SourceString: I feel like I’m talking too much… I am, aren’t I? I’m really not usually like this.//I think I’m just comfortable talking to you.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel like I’m talking too much… I am, aren’t I? I’m really not usually like this.//I think I’m just comfortable talking to you.

Text.SourceString: You will reach out to me when you need someone to talk to, right? I’ll try to be a good listener… Promise.
Text.LocalizedString: You will reach out to me when you need someone to talk to, right? I’ll try to be a good listener… Promise.

Text.SourceString: The lobster tank? I’m okay with it. For all I care, anyone can have whatever pet they want.//<portrait=annoyed>But I’m not the only one running the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: The lobster tank? I’m okay with it. For all I care, anyone can have whatever pet they want.//<portrait=annoyed>But I’m not the only one running the inn.

Text.SourceString: So how things are around the inn isn’t always up to me.//<portrait=normal>It's nice <Italic>sometimes</> 'cos who wants that burden.
Text.LocalizedString: So how things are around the inn isn’t always up to me.//<portrait=normal>It's nice <Italic>sometimes</> 'cos who wants that burden.

Text.SourceString: We used to have a rescue, but he ended up living in a mansion.//I suppose he’s used to living large now.
Text.LocalizedString: We used to have a rescue, but he ended up living in a mansion.//I suppose he’s used to living large now.

Text.SourceString: Yes! <NPCName>Taco</>! I still see him from time to time.//<portrait=normal>He followed <NPCName>Suki</> down from the forest one time and sort of lived here until he decided he liked the vineyard better.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes! <NPCName>Taco</>! I still see him from time to time.//<portrait=normal>He followed <NPCName>Suki</> down from the forest one time and sort of lived here until he decided he liked the vineyard better.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know how to say this, but…errr… Pizza is disgusting.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know how to say this, but…errr… Pizza is disgusting.

Text.SourceString: See? I knew it. Everybody has the same reaction.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t say it to anyone while they’re actually eating pizza. I’m not a monster… I’m just being honest.
Text.LocalizedString: See? I knew it. Everybody has the same reaction.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t say it to anyone while they’re actually eating pizza. I’m not a monster… I’m just being honest.

Text.SourceString: Oh, it’s you! I’m so glad to see you!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, it’s you! I’m so glad to see you!

Text.SourceString: We should hang out on the weekend or something. When you’re not too busy.
Text.LocalizedString: We should hang out on the weekend or something. When you’re not too busy.

Text.SourceString: I want to hear all about you and your day.
Text.LocalizedString: I want to hear all about you and your day.

Text.SourceString: I really can’t with <NPCName>Suki</>, sometimes. Ugh.
Text.LocalizedString: I really can’t with <NPCName>Suki</>, sometimes. Ugh.

Text.SourceString: She can be so pushy, <PlayerName>$player</>. But don’t worry, I don’t let it bother me anymore.//<portrait=normal>Inhale...exhale...
Text.LocalizedString: She can be so pushy, <PlayerName>$player</>. But don’t worry, I don’t let it bother me anymore.//<portrait=normal>Inhale...exhale...

Text.SourceString: I feel bad, but sometimes I don’t even wanna tell my sis things.//I just know that I won’t like her reaction.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel bad, but sometimes I don’t even wanna tell my sis things.//I just know that I won’t like her reaction.

Text.SourceString: <Italic>Like</>, sometimes I don’t tell her important things… I hate this feeling and having to tiptoe around.//<portrait=concerned>I wish I could just tell her everything.
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>Like</>, sometimes I don’t tell her important things… I hate this feeling and having to tiptoe around.//<portrait=concerned>I wish I could just tell her everything.

Text.SourceString: I don’t want to hide things from you, <PlayerName>$player</>… And I won’t.//You’ve never judged me, and I appreciate that.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want to hide things from you, <PlayerName>$player</>… And I won’t.//You’ve never judged me, and I appreciate that.

Text.SourceString: And let’s face it… Some of the things that I said were… Borderline mean.//A bit harsh, sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: And let’s face it… Some of the things that I said were… Borderline mean.//A bit harsh, sometimes.

Text.SourceString: You’re different, aren’t you? In a good way, I mean.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re different, aren’t you? In a good way, I mean.

Text.SourceString: You're so fun to talk to.
Text.LocalizedString: You're so fun to talk to.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard for me to admit this, but…well, we’re friends, right?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard for me to admit this, but…well, we’re friends, right?

Text.SourceString: I know that I always say how my sister can be hard and stuff, but I don’t know what I would do without her.//I don’t think I’d have survived grade school, to tell you the truth.
Text.LocalizedString: I know that I always say how my sister can be hard and stuff, but I don’t know what I would do without her.//I don’t think I’d have survived grade school, to tell you the truth.

Text.SourceString: I have to wrap up work for the week and make sure everything’s ready for <NPCName>Suki</> tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to wrap up work for the week and make sure everything’s ready for <NPCName>Suki</> tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: She hates it if everything’s not just right. I suppose that’s good, though.
Text.LocalizedString: She hates it if everything’s not just right. I suppose that’s good, though.

Text.SourceString: She only wants the best for me. I know, I know… Trust me, it’s the same old song.//But that doesn’t make <NPCName>Suki</>’s behavior okay.
Text.LocalizedString: She only wants the best for me. I know, I know… Trust me, it’s the same old song.//But that doesn’t make <NPCName>Suki</>’s behavior okay.

Text.SourceString: It’s not okay to force your opinions on other people. I told <NpcName>Suki</> that.//We’re all adults, right? We can talk it out.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not okay to force your opinions on other people. I told <NpcName>Suki</> that.//We’re all adults, right? We can talk it out.

Text.SourceString: I had a dream about you last night… I was tempted to write you a letter about it, but I…I don’t know.
Text.LocalizedString: I had a dream about you last night… I was tempted to write you a letter about it, but I…I don’t know.

Text.SourceString: No, not a nightmare. Ha ha… It was a good dream.
Text.LocalizedString: No, not a nightmare. Ha ha… It was a good dream.

Text.SourceString: Come and see me again tomorrow? We’ll talk about something fun.//Like giant meteorites.
Text.LocalizedString: Come and see me again tomorrow? We’ll talk about something fun.//Like giant meteorites.

Text.SourceString: Or I could come over to your cabin?//<portrait=happy>And we could talk about stuff… Whatever you’d rather do is fine with me.
Text.LocalizedString: Or I could come over to your cabin?//<portrait=happy>And we could talk about stuff… Whatever you’d rather do is fine with me.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I have <NPCName>Suki</>. Is she annoying sometimes? Yes.//But I can be annoying too, I’m sure.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I have <NPCName>Suki</>. Is she annoying sometimes? Yes.//But I can be annoying too, I’m sure.

Text.SourceString: Think about it… <NPCName>Suki</> and I have been living together since before we were born.//<portrait=normal>We’re bound to get on each other’s nerves, and squabbles are okay as long as we respect our boundaries.
Text.LocalizedString: Think about it… <NPCName>Suki</> and I have been living together since before we were born.//<portrait=normal>We’re bound to get on each other’s nerves, and squabbles are okay as long as we respect our boundaries.

Text.SourceString: You must be so lonely on that big farm of yours.
Text.LocalizedString: You must be so lonely on that big farm of yours.

Text.SourceString: Aww… Come and see me if you get lonely, okay? I’ll keep you company.
Text.LocalizedString: Aww… Come and see me if you get lonely, okay? I’ll keep you company.

Text.SourceString: Errr… Be honest with me, have you ever seen anything…weird on your farm?
Text.LocalizedString: Errr… Be honest with me, have you ever seen anything…weird on your farm?

Text.SourceString: I don’t know. Maybe…a large masked figure?//Why? What did you see?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know. Maybe…a large masked figure?//Why? What did you see?

Text.SourceString: What about <NPCName>Noah</>? He’s a good friend, that’s all.
Text.LocalizedString: What about <NPCName>Noah</>? He’s a good friend, that’s all.

Text.SourceString: Oh! Um… I’ve never thought about <NPCName>Noah</> that way.//<portrait=blushing>You didn’t think I was into him, did you? Because I'm not and it's important to me that you know that.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! Um… I’ve never thought about <NPCName>Noah</> that way.//<portrait=blushing>You didn’t think I was into him, did you? Because I'm not and it's important to me that you know that.

Text.SourceString: I know something better to do on Sunday… If you want, we could go hiking in the forest and…
Text.LocalizedString: I know something better to do on Sunday… If you want, we could go hiking in the forest and…

Text.SourceString: … Ah, never mind.
Text.LocalizedString: … Ah, never mind.

Text.SourceString: Find anything interesting to read, <PlayerName>$player</>? There’s plenty here.//<portrait=concerned>I wish I could just take it all over to the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: Find anything interesting to read, <PlayerName>$player</>? There’s plenty here.//<portrait=concerned>I wish I could just take it all over to the inn.

Text.SourceString: Well, of course not. I wasn’t serious. It wouldn’t fit in our inn.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, of course not. I wasn’t serious. It wouldn’t fit in our inn.

Text.SourceString: When <NpcName>Suki</> got pregnant and married <NpcName>Antonio</>, I was worried about her future.//<portrait=happy>But she's proved me wrong and become an amazing mom and business partner.
Text.LocalizedString: When <NpcName>Suki</> got pregnant and married <NpcName>Antonio</>, I was worried about her future.//<portrait=happy>But she's proved me wrong and become an amazing mom and business partner.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I feel like people underestimate me because I'm not as outgoing as <NpcName>Suki</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I feel like people underestimate me because I'm not as outgoing as <NpcName>Suki</>.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Valentina</> is such a sweet girl. I love spending time with her.//She reminds me of <NpcName>Suki</> when she was younger.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Valentina</> is such a sweet girl. I love spending time with her.//She reminds me of <NpcName>Suki</> when she was younger.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Suki</>'s divorce was hard on her, but I'm glad she's doing better now.//I hope running the inn gives her a sense of purpose and independence.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Suki</>'s divorce was hard on her, but I'm glad she's doing better now.//I hope running the inn gives her a sense of purpose and independence.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Valentina</> has been asking me to teach her how to play the piano.//<portrait=sad>I don't know how to play, but I think <NpcName>Nina</> might know. I should ask her.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Valentina</> has been asking me to teach her how to play the piano.//<portrait=sad>I don't know how to play, but I think <NpcName>Nina</> might know. I should ask her.

Text.SourceString: These boots are so comfy, I have two pair of them!//<portrait=happy>Oh, this isn't the one I wore last week. That was in <Italic>taupe</>, this is the brown one.
Text.LocalizedString: These boots are so comfy, I have two pair of them!//<portrait=happy>Oh, this isn't the one I wore last week. That was in <Italic>taupe</>, this is the brown one.

Text.SourceString: I let <NpcName>Suki</> borrow the <Italic>taupe</> one. She loves them too!
Text.LocalizedString: I let <NpcName>Suki</> borrow the <Italic>taupe</> one. She loves them too!

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Suki</>'s short is so cute! I'm gonna see if I could borrow them.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Suki</>'s short is so cute! I'm gonna see if I could borrow them.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Anne</> asked me about where <NpcName>Suki</> got <NpcName>Valentina</>'s dresses and stuff.//I wasn't sure, but I think it was <NpcName>Antonio</> who shopped for her.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Anne</> asked me about where <NpcName>Suki</> got <NpcName>Valentina</>'s dresses and stuff.//I wasn't sure, but I think it was <NpcName>Antonio</> who shopped for her.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Antonio</> gets great discount, being the owner of boutiques and all.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Antonio</> gets great discount, being the owner of boutiques and all.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Antonio</> lives at the inn part time. It makes it easier for him to see <NpcName>Valentina</>.//<portrait=happy>His <Italic>empanada</>. Ha ha! So cute.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Antonio</> lives at the inn part time. It makes it easier for him to see <NpcName>Valentina</>.//<portrait=happy>His <Italic>empanada</>. Ha ha! So cute.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Suki</> looks great with purple hair. It makes me wanna try coloring my hair too.//<portrait=annoyed>No...it's too much of a commitment. What if I didn't like it?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Suki</> looks great with purple hair. It makes me wanna try coloring my hair too.//<portrait=annoyed>No...it's too much of a commitment. What if I didn't like it?

Text.SourceString: I like this part of the beach. It's very quiet.
Text.LocalizedString: I like this part of the beach. It's very quiet.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Valentina</> is a natural at art. <NpcName>Nina</> taught her how to paint.//<portrait=happy>I can't paint to save my life and so is <NpcName>Suki</>.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Valentina</> is a natural at art. <NpcName>Nina</> taught her how to paint.//<portrait=happy>I can't paint to save my life and so is <NpcName>Suki</>.

Text.SourceString: I went to the hotspring with my sister the other day. That's where she usually catches up with her friend, <NpcName>Millie</>.//<portrait=sad>I tried to join the conversation but I don't think we clicked.
Text.LocalizedString: I went to the hotspring with my sister the other day. That's where she usually catches up with her friend, <NpcName>Millie</>.//<portrait=sad>I tried to join the conversation but I don't think we clicked.

Text.SourceString: The conversation kinda went dull.//I don't think I'll be joining them again.
Text.LocalizedString: The conversation kinda went dull.//I don't think I'll be joining them again.

Text.SourceString: I need to find my bathing suit.//<portrait=surprised>It's getting warmer. Soon, the snow will melt. Yay!
Text.LocalizedString: I need to find my bathing suit.//<portrait=surprised>It's getting warmer. Soon, the snow will melt. Yay!

Text.SourceString: I get major bloated after eating pizza. I can't.
Text.LocalizedString: I get major bloated after eating pizza. I can't.

Text.SourceString: I heard corn can grow really <Italic>really</> tall.
Text.LocalizedString: I heard corn can grow really <Italic>really</> tall.

Text.SourceString: I have to admit that when <NpcName>Suki</> was pregnant, I thought she was gonna have twins.//<portrait=surprised>Can you imagine two <NpcName>Valentina</>s? Double the <Italic>sass</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to admit that when <NpcName>Suki</> was pregnant, I thought she was gonna have twins.//<portrait=surprised>Can you imagine two <NpcName>Valentina</>s? Double the <Italic>sass</>.
